caption.text:
[very long caption, beware]
Even I'm the only daughter in this family, I've never treated like a princess by my parents. As the first daughter, I should be independent. Finding money by myself since elementary school ('cause I dont know which fun activities that I can do while I don't have TV or any entertainment things), didn't have much spare time for only play with my friends out there (ask my school friends if you dont believe!), never go walk to mall or hang out except for buy books and important things. Mutia is known as the most 'katro' girl at school 😓, especially in ES and JHS.

And here, by the time, our discussion is going more serious. Sometimes I overwhelmed by their advice, like I tired of hearing their speech (they have abundant energy to speak a lot anyway). But, there's no point I can beat them. They never compare me with anyone. Never pleased me to be someone successful by social status. Or to be anything.

They just want me to be me.

My parents are not like any ordinary mom and dad. But I know, their endless love and message built me until this time. Thank you for believe me that I can be a good girl even I'm not by your side now. I promise I'll struggle to give you glorious crown at Judgement Day, insyaallah.

Love your parents as they do. Even its hard at first time, knowing that your family aren't perfect as fairytale said, remember where you came from and where you'll go back someday.

Recaptured by @akmal.pjrrdhn
